
    There are 88,058 noun occurrences of which 70,214 are polysemous.
    The next significant hand tagging task was reported in (Bruce and Wiebe, 1994), where 2,476 usages of interest were manually assigned with sense tags from the Longman Dictionary of Contemporary English (LDOCE).
    This corpus was used in various experiments, with classification accuracies ranging from 75% to 90%, depending on the algorithm and features employed.
    The high accuracy of the LEXAS system (Ng and Lee, 1996) is due in part to the use of large corpora.
    For this system, 192,800 word occurrences have been manually tagged with senses from WordNet.
    The set of tagged words consists of the 191 most frequently occurring nouns and verbs.
    The authors mention that approximately one man-year of effort was spent in tagging the data set.
